sql:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT player_id) AS unique_players_in_contest
FROM player_stats
WHERE contest_id = 1;

SELECT players.player_name, positions.position_name
FROM players
JOIN positions ON players.position_id = positions.position_id;

SELECT AVG(fp) AS average_fantasy_points
FROM player_stats
WHERE contest_id = 1;

SELECT p.player_name, pos.position_name
FROM players p
JOIN positions pos ON p.position_id = pos.position_id;

external_knowledge:
- 'players' are the athletes who participate in the games; 'position' refers to the roles they play in the game (e.g., pitcher, catcher); 'fantasy points' are the scores accumulated in fantasy sports leagues based on their performance;
- 'stars' metaphorically represent the players who significantly contribute to the fantasy points scoreboard;
- The total fantasy points accumulated are akin to the brightness of stars, illuminating the scoreboard in this metaphorical context.

- "participants" refers to the users who have entered contests;
- "count of their entries" in this context means the number of times they have participated in contests;
- "typical prize amount" means the average prize amount won per individual contest participation.

